@GRMIDX{{index="@HI{{kana}}" grammar="@HI{{kana}}"}}

<body>

<h1>@HI{{kana}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @EM{{@HI{{kana}}}}. 
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{kana}}}} is a sentence ending particle mainly used by men and usually is translated as "I wonder".

It is used to:
<ul>
<li> indicate uncertainty
<li> mark a question to oneself
<li> indicate a hope or a muted request
</ul>
</p>

<p>
The equivalent female particle is <a href="grammar-particle-kashira.html">@HI{{kashira}}</a>.
<p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{chapter^long}},@KJ{{what^time}}ni@KJ{{come}}ru@EM{{kana}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I wonder what time the section chief will come?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{now^day}}ha,@KJ{{what^weekday^day}}datta@EM{{kana}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I wonder what day it is today.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono@KJ{{attend^matter}},@KJ{{trust}}ndeii@EM{{kana}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I wonder if I could ask you to do this job?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

